</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="88924796A5A17917BC0CEC383CF3E235" lastPageId="42" lastPageNumber="43" pageId="41" pageNumber="42" type="notes">
<paragraph id="B5B5430370955AF5644526237048611F" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="CA3D986DE975851465967702778EBDF2" lastPageId="42" lastPageNumber="43" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">
See the note above under 
<taxonomicName id="7A2EC3BD8885634FF79700A393FF3F74" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Euphorbiaceae" genus="Croton" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Croton cassinioides" order="Malpighiales" pageId="41" pageNumber="42" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="cassinioides">
<emphasis id="7B1E52FD0A2828D99DC2E013FB7CED74" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">Croton cassinioides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and its synonym 
<taxonomicName id="78295C4B84F7EA5DDCFCAFD63A8C127F" genus="C." lsidName="C. delphinianus" pageId="41" pageNumber="42" rank="species" species="delphinianus">
<emphasis id="A365CDAC6FB435B2C24465B94BEF733B" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">C. delphinianus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
regarding the 
<emphasis id="F86B4985ADEB38E21F138A2CDE791E4F" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">Scott-Elliot 1557</emphasis>
specimen (P00133052, upper right), which was 
<pageBreakToken id="5FCD6BC4B302A76F124D8DF62BA1D05A" pageId="42" pageNumber="43" start="start">also</pageBreakToken>
cited by 
<bibRefCitation id="7FC9424B6682BD3C5BC57C6094C8C354" author="Baillon, H" journalOrPublisher="Adansonia" pageId="71" pageNumber="72" refId="B5" refString="Baillon, H, 1891a. Liste des plantes de Madagascar. Bulletin Mensuel de la Societe Linneenne de Paris 2: 926-928, 966-968, 977-979." title="Liste des plantes de Madagascar. Bulletin Mensuel de la Societe Linneenne de Paris 2: 926 - 928, 966 - 968, 977 - 979." year="1891 a">Baillon (1891a)</bibRefCitation>
as a syntype of 
<taxonomicName id="291458B8FD070F8A9440E8997EE34687" genus="C." lsidName="C. lasiopyrus" pageId="42" pageNumber="43" rank="species" species="lasiopyrus">
<emphasis id="CB6E3AF619BE1A3DA24269807DCA719D" italics="true" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">C. lasiopyrus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName id="AD87449F4CE8D020649D686FA8B5B5BF" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Euphorbiaceae" genus="Croton" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Croton cassinioides" order="Malpighiales" pageId="42" pageNumber="43" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="cassinioides">
<emphasis id="54532A72EEF981A9DB381C61F05A60B3" italics="true" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">Croton cassinioides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="B2A4B9474ADB8A082657D790E71F870B" genus="C." lsidName="C. lasiopyrus" pageId="42" pageNumber="43" rank="species" species="lasiopyrus">
<emphasis id="7C5FF38190BCE23F0C93460F8454A306" italics="true" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">C. lasiopyrus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are sufficiently different that they are not easily confused; the former has smaller (1.5-6 
<normalizedToken id="0B26D6E54B3C922E8AA148265B90747E" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
0.7-3 cm) elliptic leaves with dentate to subentire margins and grows in littoral zones near sea level, while the latter has larger (4-15.5 
<normalizedToken id="06DE7A242A4F95BFC724D889303FC69E" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
2.5-7 cm) obovate leaves with entire margins and grows in moist montane forests.
</paragraph>
